257
00:12:33,649 --> 00:12:35,349
They're supposed to laugh, but they're applauding instead.

258
00:12:35,449 --> 00:12:36,779
I will hate you!

259
00:12:37,179 --> 00:12:40,048
(The transfer students are touched by Ho Dong's cute act?)

260
00:12:40,049 --> 00:12:42,289
- I'm a little bit nervous.
- Right?

261
00:12:42,619 --> 00:12:44,158
- It feels strange for some reason.
- You see...

262
00:12:44,159 --> 00:12:46,789
- Right.
- I've never felt this vibe before.

263
00:12:47,289 --> 00:12:49,159
- I've only sung on stage before.
- That's right.

264
00:12:49,259 --> 00:12:52,398
- A show with a live audience...
- Usually, we begin like this,

265
00:12:52,399 --> 00:12:54,469
and then we welcome our guests.

266
00:12:54,569 --> 00:12:56,868
But today, we have 500 transfer students here.

267
00:12:56,869 --> 00:12:58,239
- Exactly.
- Right.

268
00:12:58,339 --> 00:13:00,009
We're getting an amazing vibe here.

269
00:13:00,209 --> 00:13:01,368
This is really nice.

270
00:13:01,369 --> 00:13:03,379
Many of them came from far away.

271
00:13:03,479 --> 00:13:05,578
We used to say we had a long way to reach 500 episodes,

272
00:13:05,579 --> 00:13:07,408
and the day actually came.

273
00:13:07,409 --> 00:13:09,279
- Exactly. This is hard to believe.
- Right.

274
00:13:09,379 --> 00:13:11,679
- I'm a little touched too.
- I know.

275
00:13:11,749 --> 00:13:14,319
I didn't know they'd cheer so loudly for us.

276
00:13:14,389 --> 00:13:16,788
Seeing the transfer students,

277
00:13:16,789 --> 00:13:19,658
I realized that all age groups watch our show.

278
00:13:19,659 --> 00:13:21,389
- Exactly.
- If you look at the audience...

279
00:13:21,859 --> 00:13:23,699
- Right.
- Ma'am, did you watch it often?

280
00:13:24,299 --> 00:13:25,599
What did we do last week?

281
00:13:26,099 --> 00:13:28,368
(He checks the affection for Men on a Mission unexpectedly.)

282
00:13:28,369 --> 00:13:30,669
- Today, we...
- Look at her.

283
00:13:31,099 --> 00:13:33,008
- She remembers everything.
- I saw the episode.

284
00:13:33,009 --> 00:13:35,708
But major age group of our viewers are far younger than them.

285
00:13:35,709 --> 00:13:38,478
- I wish little kids were here.
- Right.

286
00:13:38,479 --> 00:13:39,548
I'm in high school.

287
00:13:39,549 --> 00:13:41,008
- I'm in middle school.
- We have a high school student.

288
00:13:41,009 --> 00:13:42,208
I'm in 12th grade!

289
00:13:42,209 --> 00:13:43,579
- You're in 12th grade?
- 12th grade?

290
00:13:44,019 --> 00:13:45,249
I'm in 11th grade.

291
00:13:45,719 --> 00:13:47,489
That's not what I meant. We...

292
00:13:47,789 --> 00:13:49,418
- What?
- Gosh, he startled me.

293
00:13:49,419 --> 00:13:51,459
- What's going on?
- Everyone!

294
00:13:51,989 --> 00:13:54,128
- Everyone!
- What's going on?

295
00:13:54,129 --> 00:13:56,498
- What's going on?
- Hi!

296
00:13:56,499 --> 00:13:58,499
(Leeteuk, the special Senior Teuk)

297
00:14:00,169 --> 00:14:01,768
(Oh, my. He's so handsome!)

298
00:14:01,769 --> 00:14:02,839
Oh, he's joining us.

299
00:14:04,569 --> 00:14:05,598
It's good to see you again!

300
00:14:05,599 --> 00:14:08,309
Make some noise!

301
00:14:09,609 --> 00:14:11,238
My goodness. What's going on?

302
00:14:11,239 --> 00:14:13,178
- I'm the special senior student...
- This is amazing.

303
00:14:13,179 --> 00:14:14,948
who comes whenever there's a special event at Brother School.

304
00:14:14,949 --> 00:14:16,978
I'm not Leedeuk.

305
00:14:16,979 --> 00:14:18,318
I'm not Taxi.

306
00:14:18,319 --> 00:14:20,018
I am Senior Teuk!

307
00:14:20,019 --> 00:14:22,389
(I am Senior Teuk.)

308
00:14:23,989 --> 00:14:25,759
- What's that?
- By the way,

309
00:14:26,089 --> 00:14:27,828
you brought a lot of documents. What are those?

310
00:14:27,829 --> 00:14:30,529
To celebrate the 500th episode of Men on a Mission,

311
00:14:30,699 --> 00:14:33,429
- you invited 500 transfer students.
- Yes.

312
00:14:33,669 --> 00:14:37,239
People in all areas of the country wanted to be here today,

313
00:14:37,439 --> 00:14:39,839
so we received nearly 10,000 transfer applications.

314
00:14:40,539 --> 00:14:42,138
- Oh, that's a lot.
- Are those transfer applications?

315
00:14:42,139 --> 00:14:43,408
Yes, they are.

316
00:14:43,409 --> 00:14:46,409
We selected only 500 applicants with good grades,

317
00:14:46,609 --> 00:14:48,349
and those 500 students are here.

318
00:14:48,509 --> 00:14:50,718
Give them a round of applause!

319
00:14:50,719 --> 00:14:52,719
- That's amazing.
- They're incredible.

320
00:14:56,659 --> 00:14:59,228
Also, some of them have special stories...

321
00:14:59,229 --> 00:15:01,829
- where they met one of you.
- What?

322
00:15:01,959 --> 00:15:03,658
- Some of them have met us?
- They have met us before?

323
00:15:03,659 --> 00:15:05,629
- Really?
- Let me hold this.

324
00:15:05,799 --> 00:15:08,198
- I wonder what stories they have.
- Oh, really?

325
00:15:08,199 --> 00:15:10,299
- First up! Oh, here he is.
- They all seem excited.

326
00:15:10,499 --> 00:15:12,169
Where are you, Seong Hwan?

327
00:15:16,739 --> 00:15:17,909
- Over there.
- There he is.

328
00:15:18,509 --> 00:15:19,578
Is his name Seong Ha Na?

329
00:15:19,579 --> 00:15:21,208
Seong Hwan, before we start,

330
00:15:21,209 --> 00:15:22,719
- Oh, it's Seong Hwan.
- can you introduce yourself?

331
00:15:23,249 --> 00:15:26,719
Hello. I'm Choi Seong Hwan, and I'm from Gangneung.

332
00:15:28,249 --> 00:15:29,418
It's nice to meet you.

333
00:15:29,419 --> 00:15:30,618
- Gangneung?
- If he's from Gangneung...

334
00:15:30,619 --> 00:15:32,258
- Hee Chul is from there too.
- Yes, he is.

335
00:15:32,259 --> 00:15:33,929
- Hee Chul is from Wonju.
- I'm from Wonju.

336
00:15:34,889 --> 00:15:36,958
Which of the members have you met?

337
00:15:36,959 --> 00:15:41,329
- I've met Ho Dong before.
- You've met Ho Dong?

338
00:15:41,429 --> 00:15:42,839
- We have a victim of Ho Dong here.
- What?

339
00:15:42,969 --> 00:15:44,168
A victim of Ho Dong is here.

340
00:15:44,169 --> 00:15:45,169
(Another victim of Ho Dong is here?)

341
00:15:45,339 --> 00:15:47,138
- In Gangneung...
- Did you appear on "Star King?"

342
00:15:47,139 --> 00:15:49,279
- Not long ago...
- Did he, really?

343
00:15:49,509 --> 00:15:50,838
Ho Dong never went to Gangneung.

344
00:15:50,839 --> 00:15:53,709
- I hope that's not the case.
- Ask him if he came on "Star King."

345
00:15:53,909 --> 00:15:54,978
Let's hear him out.

346
00:15:54,979 --> 00:15:56,879
- How did you meet him? I'm curious.
- I mean...

347
00:15:57,319 --> 00:15:58,879
- Ask him yourself.
- I never went on "Star King."

348
00:15:58,979 --> 00:16:01,089
- He didn't go on "Star King."
- That's a relief.

349
00:16:01,349 --> 00:16:03,159
Is it a good story or a bad story?

350
00:16:03,289 --> 00:16:04,819
It's a heartwarming story.

351
00:16:06,889 --> 00:16:08,189
Jang Hoon, say what you always say.

352
00:16:09,029 --> 00:16:10,498
"What's the point of hearing a heartwarming story about him?"

353
00:16:10,499 --> 00:16:12,699
We went to Gangneung to shoot "2 Days 1 Night."

354
00:16:12,969 --> 00:16:14,528
A kid asked for your autograph,

355
00:16:14,529 --> 00:16:15,699
but you told him to go away. Maybe he's the kid.

356
00:16:15,769 --> 00:16:17,138
(Mysterious stories are created endlessly.)

357
00:16:17,139 --> 00:16:18,698
- The guy from Gangneung...
- I didn't say that.

358
00:16:18,699 --> 00:16:21,008
- I said to meet me after the shoot.
- Right.

359
00:16:21,009 --> 00:16:22,939
The guy from Gangneung, I'm sorry, but sit down.

360
00:16:23,979 --> 00:16:25,539
- Sit down if it's a touching story.
- Right.

361
00:16:26,249 --> 00:16:28,078
- You say only bad things here.
- Let's be kind...

362
00:16:28,079 --> 00:16:30,178
- and hear what happened.
- Right. Let's hear his story.

363
00:16:30,179 --> 00:16:31,418
Seong Hwan, please tell us.

364
00:16:31,419 --> 00:16:32,619
- How did we meet?
- How did you meet him?

365
00:16:32,919 --> 00:16:35,348
Seven years ago, I worked at a sashimi restaurant.

366
00:16:35,349 --> 00:16:36,589
And Ho Dong...

367
00:16:37,189 --> 00:16:40,058
I saw a big man wrapped in a shirt like this...

368
00:16:40,059 --> 00:16:41,529
running from the parking lot.

369
00:16:41,859 --> 00:16:43,999
I looked at him, wondering who he was.

370
00:16:44,159 --> 00:16:46,999
But then the restaurant owner told me to go upstairs.

371
00:16:47,199 --> 00:16:49,638
- Ho Dong's family was there.
- Oh, I see.

372
00:16:49,639 --> 00:16:51,169
- At the sashimi restaurant?
- Yes.

373
00:16:51,369 --> 00:16:53,809
I served their table by myself.

374
00:16:54,069 --> 00:16:56,409
While I was waiting, Ho Dong asked me to come.

375
00:16:56,639 --> 00:16:58,239
I sat down next to him, and we talked.

376
00:16:58,509 --> 00:17:01,448
- Ho Dong asked about me.
- Yes.

377
00:17:01,449 --> 00:17:03,049
And I said I would enlist in the military in the next month.

378
00:17:03,249 --> 00:17:04,318
Since I would enlist in the military,

379
00:17:04,319 --> 00:17:06,488
he told me to be safe while serving in the military.

380
00:17:06,489 --> 00:17:08,119
And he gave me 50 dollars as pocket money.

381
00:17:10,019 --> 00:17:11,758
- That's nice of him.
- Right.

382
00:17:11,759 --> 00:17:12,828
(He flexed on the future soldier who would go through a hard time.)

383
00:17:12,829 --> 00:17:14,628
- Ho Dong, do you remember that?
- Ho Dong...

384
00:17:14,629 --> 00:17:16,728
- Do you remember that?
- He offered...

385
00:17:16,729 --> 00:17:17,999
- to take a photo with me.
- That must be true.

386
00:17:18,099 --> 00:17:19,099
Why did he do that?

387
00:17:19,399 --> 00:17:21,428
- We took a selfie together.
- Really?

388
00:17:21,429 --> 00:17:22,798
(Ho Dong volunteered to take a photo with him.)

389
00:17:22,799 --> 00:17:23,899
- A photo...
- You see...

390
00:17:23,999 --> 00:17:26,808
I don't remember exactly what happened,

391
00:17:26,809 --> 00:17:29,008
but I'm sure that I wanted to give him good energy...

392
00:17:29,009 --> 00:17:32,239
- as he seemed like a nice guy.
- I see.

393
00:17:32,509 --> 00:17:34,148
- Nice.
- That's nice of you.

394
00:17:34,149 --> 00:17:36,279
But as far as I remember, didn't I give you 500 dollars?

395
00:17:36,849 --> 00:17:38,319
- Five hundred dollars?
- You gave me fifty dollars.

396
00:17:38,979 --> 00:17:40,388
(He failed to increase the amount by 10 times.)

397
00:17:40,389 --> 00:17:41,719
It would've been a lot thicker.

398
00:17:41,989 --> 00:17:43,059
You gave me 50 dollars.

399
00:17:43,619 --> 00:17:45,088
The amount of money doesn't matter since he was so caring.

400
00:17:45,089 --> 00:17:46,989
- It's nice of him.
- Of course. It's nice of him.

401
00:17:47,089 --> 00:17:49,189
Thank you for remembering that.

402
00:17:49,259 --> 00:17:51,599
I should be thanking you too. I spent the money...

403
00:17:52,029 --> 00:17:53,099
on buying something delicious.

404
00:17:53,799 --> 00:17:54,998
- That's so nice of him.
- That's nice of him.

405
00:17:54,999 --> 00:17:56,938
- Thank you.
- Thank you.

406
00:17:56,939 --> 00:17:58,238
Thank you, Seong Hwan.

407
00:17:58,239 --> 00:18:00,339
- It was a trivial thing, - Right.

408
00:18:00,439 --> 00:18:02,508
- but it remained as a good memory.
- Let's meet the next friend.

409
00:18:02,509 --> 00:18:04,339
- Next up is... Oh, it's him.
- That was really great of him.

410
00:18:04,479 --> 00:18:06,708
Where is Seung Yeon? Where are you, Kim Seung Yeon?

411
00:18:06,709 --> 00:18:08,378
There was an MC...

412
00:18:08,379 --> 00:18:09,419
Oh, there he is.

413
00:18:09,649 --> 00:18:11,679
Please introduce yourself. Which one of them have you met?

414
00:18:13,289 --> 00:18:16,589
Hi. I'm Seung Yeon, and I'm from Seoul.

415
00:18:17,089 --> 00:18:18,318
(Which of the members has Seung Yeon met before?)

416
00:18:18,319 --> 00:18:19,729
Which member have you met before?

417
00:18:20,029 --> 00:18:22,129
I have a connection with Jang Hoon.

418
00:18:23,299 --> 00:18:24,458
- Jang Hoon?
- Me?

419
00:18:24,459 --> 00:18:25,528
I knew this would happen.

420
00:18:25,529 --> 00:18:26,828
(Jang Hoon will be tried based on the story.)

421
00:18:26,829 --> 00:18:27,968
- Seung Yeon seems...
- I wonder how they met.

422
00:18:27,969 --> 00:18:29,368
- Seung Yeon seems very angry.
- I wonder what story he has.

423
00:18:29,369 --> 00:18:31,298
- He sounds very determined.
- Indeed.

424
00:18:31,299 --> 00:18:32,769
How did you meet Jang Hoon?

425
00:18:33,409 --> 00:18:36,239
It's actually my father who met him.

426
00:18:37,109 --> 00:18:39,649
- My father is...
- Was he a basketball player?

427
00:18:40,349 --> 00:18:41,379
a former basketball player.

428
00:18:42,679 --> 00:18:43,778
- And...
- Of course.

429
00:18:43,779 --> 00:18:45,988
In his school days, Jang Hoon was his rival.

430
00:18:45,989 --> 00:18:47,248
- They were rivals?
- In his school days?

431
00:18:47,249 --> 00:18:49,788
- But Jang Hoon doesn't think of...
- I'm sorry,

432
00:18:49,789 --> 00:18:51,758
but are you sure you're not mistaken?

433
00:18:51,759 --> 00:18:53,089
I never had a rival.

434
00:18:54,159 --> 00:18:55,829
(Awesome)

435
00:18:56,199 --> 00:18:59,669
(His confidence overwhelms all 500 audience members.)

436
00:19:00,169 --> 00:19:01,298
(Chuckling)

437
00:19:01,299 --> 00:19:03,238
- What kind of rivalry...
- Jang Hoon always says...

438
00:19:03,239 --> 00:19:04,369
that his greatest rival was himself.

439
00:19:04,839 --> 00:19:06,769
I wonder what kind of rivalry we had.

440
00:19:06,839 --> 00:19:08,008
- His family name is Kim.
- Who could he be?

441
00:19:08,009 --> 00:19:09,038
My father is...

442
00:19:09,039 --> 00:19:10,609
- I'll just tell you his name.
- Okay.

443
00:19:10,709 --> 00:19:11,938
He was a basketball player at Korea University.

444
00:19:11,939 --> 00:19:13,078
His name is Kim Byong Chul.

445
00:19:13,079 --> 00:19:14,609
(Korea University's basketball player Kim Byong Chul)

446
00:19:14,949 --> 00:19:16,279
His name is Kim Byong Chul.

447
00:19:19,489 --> 00:19:23,189
(The 3-point shooter who led Korea University's heyday)

448
00:19:23,989 --> 00:19:27,889
(The essence of high-flying basketball)

449
00:19:28,929 --> 00:19:32,129
("If Kim Byong Chul Goes Crazy, the Others Can Just Run Back and Forth")

450
00:19:33,069 --> 00:19:35,769
(Flying Peter Pan, Kim Byong Chul)

451
00:19:36,239 --> 00:19:37,598
Oh, I see!

452
00:19:37,599 --> 00:19:39,298
- So, - Peter Pan.

453
00:19:39,299 --> 00:19:40,808
I can't see you because you're too far away.

454
00:19:40,809 --> 00:19:42,738
You're Byong Chul's son?

455
00:19:42,739 --> 00:19:43,938
We don't really look alike.

456
00:19:43,939 --> 00:19:46,079
In my family, looking like my dad is an insult.

457
00:19:46,949 --> 00:19:48,548
(His son publicly insults his looks.)

458
00:19:48,549 --> 00:19:52,278
Hey, your dad was such a great player.

459
00:19:52,279 --> 00:19:55,248
He was the best. I really like him as a person.

460
00:19:55,249 --> 00:19:57,289
But there's something that you're mistaken about.

461
00:19:57,419 --> 00:19:58,919
He wasn't my rival.

462
00:19:58,959 --> 00:20:00,488
Then, whose rival are you?

463
00:20:00,489 --> 00:20:01,788
- Seung Yeon.
- Who is it?

464
00:20:01,789 --> 00:20:03,198
Well, Seung Yeon, we have to be precise about this.

465
00:20:03,199 --> 00:20:06,698
Even though you're the son of a guy I really like...

466
00:20:06,699 --> 00:20:08,068
- Of course.
- "I'm me."

467
00:20:08,069 --> 00:20:10,068
Anyway, I'm so happy to see you.

468
00:20:10,069 --> 00:20:11,439
- Nice to meet you.
- He was taken aback.

469
00:20:11,539 --> 00:20:12,598
- It's so nice to see you, so...
- Seung Yeon.

470
00:20:12,599 --> 00:20:14,038
- All of us at Men on a Mission...
- That's so nice.

471
00:20:14,039 --> 00:20:15,868
were fans of your dad, Kim Byong Chul.

472
00:20:15,869 --> 00:20:17,078
- Oh, really?
- Yes.

473
00:20:17,079 --> 00:20:18,978
- I loved him so much.
- Really.

474
00:20:18,979 --> 00:20:22,648
He was a great player who represented that era.

475
00:20:22,649 --> 00:20:25,048
So, you should be good to your dad. Listen to what he says.

476
00:20:25,049 --> 00:20:26,688
- Yes, of course.
- Yes.

477
00:20:26,689 --> 00:20:27,918
- Right. It's nice to meet you.
- You really should.

478
00:20:27,919 --> 00:20:30,359
- Welcome!
- Thank you, Seung Yeon!

479
00:20:31,089 --> 00:20:32,319
This is fun.

480
00:20:32,389 --> 00:20:33,928
Let's meet our next friend.

481
00:20:33,929 --> 00:20:37,098
Next, it's Seo Hyun. Cho Seo Hyun, where are you?

482
00:20:37,099 --> 00:20:38,698
- Seo Hyun?
- Here.

483
00:20:38,699 --> 00:20:40,028
- Hi, Seo Hyun.
- Please introduce yourself.

484
00:20:40,029 --> 00:20:41,168
Hi, guys.

485
00:20:41,169 --> 00:20:44,898
I am Cho Seo Hyun, and I transferred from Yeonsinnae.

486
00:20:44,899 --> 00:20:47,038
- Nice to meet you.
- She's so cute.

487
00:20:47,039 --> 00:20:48,638
- You're from nearby.
- Who do you have a connection to?

488
00:20:48,639 --> 00:20:49,639
If it's Yeonsinnae...

489
00:20:49,640 --> 00:20:52,078
I have a connection to Yeong Cheol...

490
00:20:52,079 --> 00:20:53,849
Thanks! We enjoyed hearing from you!

491
00:20:54,479 --> 00:20:56,049
Who's our next friend?

492
00:20:56,349 --> 00:20:58,519
You have to stay strong and talk.

493
00:20:58,679 --> 00:21:00,288
- We'll continue to root for you.
- Sit. Yes.

494
00:21:00,289 --> 00:21:01,718
Seo Hyun, what kind of connection do we have?

495
00:21:01,719 --> 00:21:03,158
Have we met before?

496
00:21:03,159 --> 00:21:06,958
Well, actually, we haven't met in person...

497
00:21:06,959 --> 00:21:08,558
- That's a relief.
- It is.

498
00:21:08,559 --> 00:21:09,959
(Chuckling)

499
